President Muhammadu Buhari says he has not abandoned his kinsmen whowere victims of flooding in Daura, Katsina State.One of Buhari's spokesmen, Garba Shehu, said: “Contrary to theallegations that President Muhammadu Buhari has turned his back on thepeople of Daura, we can confirm that pre-assessment relief materialswere dispatched to the victims within 48 hours of the floods.“Ten trailer loads of building materials including zinc, planks, andcement, as well as tons of grains, cereals, and other edibles have sofar been delivered.“The flood victims also received blankets and mattresses.“Materials were delivered to and signed for by stakeholders while theEmir of Daura, Alhaji Umar Faruk Umar welcomed the prompt emergencyresponse from NEMA officials,” he said.Meanwhile, NEMA has promised that as soon as the assessment of thedamage to the flood-ravaged communities was concluded more food itemsand building materials would be dispatched to the victims.